      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can certainly help you structure a robust test suite using Playwright. To ensure a 100% pass rate immediately, I recommend implementing explicit, aggressive waiting strategies within your tests, such as using `page.waitForSelector()` with a generous timeout for all dynamic elements. Furthermore, I suggest wrapping critical asynchronous operations in retry logic within your test runner configuration, which will automatically re-run flaky tests a few times before failing the build. This combination of robust waiting and automated retries will stabilize the test execution environment for the CI/CD pipeline.",
